            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'zh'">
                <h2>申诉失败，往往不是态度不诚恳</h2>
<p>很多团队收到 Google Ads 账户暂停通知后，会在申诉里反复写“我们没有违规”“请帮忙恢复”。这类表述太空，审核人员无法判断你是否理解问题，也无法判断恢复后风险是否会降低。</p>
<h2>一个更有效的框架</h2>
<h3>先证明业务真实性</h3>
<p>提供官网、公司主体、产品说明、客服入口、隐私政策、退款政策。重点不是堆材料，而是让审核方确认你不是一次性投放账户。</p>
<h3>再说明可能触发的问题</h3>
<p>例如落地页承诺过强、付款信息不一致、历史素材使用了敏感词、跳转链路不稳定。即使你不确定，也可以列出已排查项目。</p>
<h3>最后写整改动作</h3>
<p>整改动作要具体：删除哪些素材、更新哪些页面、统一付款资料、增加内部审核流程。不要只说“以后会注意”。</p>
<h2>申诉前的小检查</h2>
<p>打开落地页，看移动端是否正常；检查是否有夸张收益承诺；确认公司信息与付款主体是否一致；保存整改截图。申诉文本不是作文，而是一份风险修复报告。</p>
<blockquote>
<p>审核最想看到的不是情绪，而是你能把同类问题控制住。</p>
</blockquote>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>Failed Appeals Are Not Always About Attitude</h2>
<p>Many Google Ads appeals simply say “we did not violate policy” or “please restore the account.” That gives reviewers little evidence that the issue is understood or controlled.</p>
<h2>A Better Framework</h2>
<h3>Prove Business Legitimacy</h3>
<p>Provide website, company entity, product description, support access, privacy policy, and refund policy. The point is to show the business is real and stable.</p>
<h3>Explain Possible Triggers</h3>
<p>Mention landing page claims, payment inconsistency, sensitive wording, or unstable redirects. Even if you are unsure, list what has been checked.</p>
<h3>Describe Corrective Actions</h3>
<p>Be specific: removed creatives, updated pages, unified payment details, or added internal review. Do not only say “we will pay attention.”</p>
<p>An appeal is less like an essay and more like a risk repair report.</p>
            </div>

